            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Both `:terminal` and `:!` are halfway there. I can see the output very clearly and a clean way.\r\n\r\n```txt\r\n 1 Run options: include {:locations=>{\"./spec/koine/attributes/attributes_spec.rb\"=>[83]}}                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     \r\n 2 .                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                           \r\n 3                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n 4 Finished in 0.00107 seconds (files took 0.07467 seconds to load)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            \r\n 5 1 example, 0 failures                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       \r\n 6                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n 7                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             \r\n 8 [Process exited 0]    \r\n```\r\n\r\nI don't need to run it in the same terminal. In fact, once I run a test I don't care about the previous test message. As you can see in the output, once I hit a key, the output is gone and I cannot quickly reopen it, so I can read it once again.\r\n\r\nIf there is a way of opening last terminal output in full screen and go back to my code with just an few key strokes as I do with `<c-z>` and `fg` I probably don't need this proposed feature.\r\n\r\n",
