            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Another reason why the old vim behavior was powerful - being able to run a command in the terminal by putting the editor in the background - is seeing the output in full terminal size, regardless of how many splits.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/226834/c382d873-1ad9-4f9c-8fa5-0927ee33152c)\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/226834/ecb8d076-3377-4798-90d4-fa88d17bc618)\r\n\r\n\r\nThe `:term` behaviour will make the output fit to the buffer size, and it does not handle line breaks very well...\r\n\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/226834/6a9c5c2a-7215-4ba5-8610-30e415238d07)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCopy and paste of the lines:\r\n\r\n```\r\n _____________________________\r\n____________ \r\n/ Hello nvim community, how ar\r\ne you folks \\\r\n\\ doing today?                \r\n            /\r\n -----------------------------\r\n------------ \r\n        \\   ^__^\r\n         \\  (oo)\\_______\r\n            (__)\\       )\\/\\\r\n                ||----w |\r\n                ||     ||\r\n\r\n[Process exited 0]\r\n```\r\n",
